A member of the Sokoto State House of Assembly, Alhaji Isa Harisu, yesterday slumped and died after he arrived at the office complex to attend the day’s plenary. Deputy Speaker Abubakar Magaji, who confirmed Harisu’s death, said the lawmaker, a member of the All Progressives Congress (APC), who represented Kebbe constituency, was rushed to Usmanu Danfodiyo University Teaching Hospital after he slumped in the morning. “When he slumped, he was rushed to the hospital, but he died on the way,” Magaji said. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the incident was officially announced at the plenary by Magaji. Family sources indicated that the late lawmaker, aged 55, left behind his mother, four wives and 22 children. Meanwhile, the Assembly shifted its sitting to today to attend the burial rites scheduled to take place yesterday. 